## dma-coherent

Property name: `dma-coherent`

Value type: `<empty>`

For architectures which are by default non-coherent for I/O, the _dma-coherent_ property is used to indicate a device is capable of coherent DMA operations. Some architectures have coherent DMA by default and this property is not applicable.

---

**Source:** Linux kernel Documentation\n\n```\n- dma-coherent: Present if dma operations are coherent.


A example of HiKey board hi6220 SoC specific DT entry:
